<subSubSection id="BD86654EFF8F796EFF1FADB5FD84FCFA" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F52336C5FF8F796EFF1FADB5FD84FCFA" blockId="1.[151,1436,533,1041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis id="C7E8EAD7FF8F796EFF1FADB5FE85FD3C" bold="true" box="[199,316,706,729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="329C4D46FF8F796EFE90ADB6FE5AFD3C" box="[328,483,705,729]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Boalda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gyona">
<emphasis id="C7E8EAD7FF8F796EFE90ADB6FE5AFD3C" box="[328,483,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Boalda gyona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily distinguished from its congeners by the mottled appearance, dark russet coloration, larger size (forewing length 
<quantity id="32649B20FF8F796EFD89AD92FD01FD19" box="[593,696,741,764]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" unit="mm" value="10.5">10.5 mm</quantity>
), and robustness of the male clasper and the expansiveness of the secondary lobe deriving from the costa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BD86654EFF8F796EFF1FAC5DFCACFC0A" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" type="description">
<paragraph id="F52336C5FF8F796EFF1FAC5DFCACFC0A" blockId="1.[151,1436,533,1041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis id="C7E8EAD7FF8F796EFF1FAC5DFEF2FCA4" bold="true" box="[199,331,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Description</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="6DA72A40FF8F796EFE83AC5DFE16FCA4" box="[347,431,810,833]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="3.[151,244,1786,1808]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,214,1749]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 10. Male genitalia, Boalda gyona holotype male. Brazil: Santa Catarina. USNM Slide 51499. a, valves; b, phallus. FIGURE 11. Male genitalia, Boalda pulcherrima male. Argentina: Tucumàn. USNM Slide 148043. a, valves; b, phallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/804775/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Figs 10</figureCitation>
a, b; cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="910D4B34FF8F796EFDD3AC5DFD32FCA4" author="Todd" box="[523,651,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" refString="Todd, E. L. (1961) A note on the systematic position of Boalda gyona Schaus (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 63, 261." type="journal article" year="1961">Todd, 1961</bibRefCitation>
: 261, 
<figureCitation id="6DA72A40FF8F796EFD17AC5DFCB6FCA4" box="[719,783,810,833]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="0.[151,244,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,1177,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@0.[150,1436,1177,1820]" captionTargetPageId="0" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution of recorded and reported Boalda species. ● B. gyona: Santa Catarina, Brazil (type locality); Quebrada de los Cuervos, Uruguay, reported by Biezanko et al. (1957) * San Miguel de Tucumàn, Argentina, type locality of Nephelistis pulcherrima ▲ Parque Nacional Teniente Enciso, Depto. Boquerón, Paraguay, type locality of Boalda poguei. ̍ Parque Nacional Cerro Corá, Depto. Amambay, Paraguay, collection locality of Boalda sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/804771/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="C7E8EAD7FF8F796EFCF0AC5EFC74FCA4" box="[808,973,809,833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Valves expanded apically, with secondary nearly cordate flap on ventral surface overlapping valve for more than 75 percent of the area between the base of the clasper to its apex; inner margin of valve produced posteromedially towards juxta; juxta rhomboidal; valves setose apically; pronounced thorn-like clasper arising medially; wispy tuft of setae arising from margin at base of clasper; saccus blunt; pleural sclerite S-shaped; uncus of uniform width; phallus simple, without cornuti but vesica with sclerotized basal cap-shaped plate bearing 8 to 10 denticles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
